sequenceDiagram
  autonumber
  participant U as 🌐 User
  participant H as 🔐 Auth0 and Easy Auth
  participant S as 📊 Streamlit Dashboard
  participant K as 🔑 Azure Table Storage
  participant A as ⚡ FastAPI Export API
  participant D as 🗄️ Databricks SQL

  U->>H: Sign in to dashboard
  H-->>S: Authorized email identity
  U->>S: Open API Access and create personal key
  S->>K: Store HMAC hash with owner metadata
  K-->>S: Saved key record
  S-->>U: Show raw gems_live key once and API base URL
  U->>A: Call /versions or /export/table.csv with X-API-Key
  A->>K: Validate hash revoked status and owner allowlist
  K-->>A: Key is active
  A->>D: Query allowed table in gems_catalog.gold_v1
  D-->>A: Version metadata rows or CSV rows
  A-->>U: JSON or CSV response
  Note over S,D: Dashboard pages may also query Databricks directly for Explore and Modeling
